EBNF is a *syntactic metalanguage*.

The syntax of Algol 60 was defined with BNF (Backus Naur Form)

EBNF is useful to define the grammar of programming languages.


An EBNF grammar consists of rules(?)

    name: production

 or informally

    rule: rule1, "keyword", rule2, rule3


------

  The official ISO EBNF spec (ISO/IEC 14977:1996) can be freely downloaded from the ISO website https://standards.iso.org/ittf/PubliclyAvailableStandards/index.html
